OL,3,C'Gross failure' in hospital care may
OL,4,Chave contributed to disabled woman's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FBut the inquest into Ms Every's death
OL,8,Frevealed "failures" in the care she
OL,9,Freceived in hospital ` including the
OL,10,Fprescription of morphine, which can
OL,11,Fcause respiratory problems for people
OL,12,Fwith MD, the absence of specialist
OL,13,Flearning disability nurses to assist
OL,14,Fher in communicating with staff, and
OL,15,Fthe administration of an enema to Ms
OL,16,FEvery when she was seemingly asleep
OL,17,Fand unable to consent.
OL,26,@pD@JOUpD@SO]
