OL,3,C'Gross failure' in hospital care may
OL,4,Chave contributed to disabled woman's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,F"We have the absence of any evidence
OL,8,Fto justify the prescription of
OL,9,Fmorphine; the significant and
OL,10,Ffrequently observed laxes in the
OL,11,Fobservation of vulnerable patients;
OL,12,Fand the absence of anything
OL,13,Fapproaching consent for what is a very
OL,14,Finvasive and intimate procedure."
OL,16,FMs Every's death was caused by
OL,17,Fcomplications of a cardiac arrest the
OL,18,Fcoroner said was "probably"
OL,19,Fcontributed to by the morphine given
OL,20,Fto Ms Every in treatment for bowel
OL,21,Fcancer.
