OL,7,F"Had the nursing staff provided clear
OL,8,Fand contemporary records of their
OL,9,Fdecision-making in relation to the
OL,10,Ftreatment of Chloe, it's entirely
OL,11,Fpossible that I would have been able
OL,12,Fto consider expert pathological
OL,13,Fevidence that could assist me in
OL,14,Funderstanding the mechanism of Chloe's
OL,15,Fdeath."
OL,17,FHe added: "I am concerned these are
OL,18,Factions and events that did not take
OL,19,Fplace in isolation."
