OL,7,FCaron Heyes, a solicitor on behalf of
OL,8,FMs Every's family, said in a
OL,9,Fstatement: "I cannot forgive or forget
OL,10,Fthat Chloe died after terrible care
OL,11,Fthat marred her last days which should
OL,12,Fhave been spent in peace with her
OL,13,Ffamily, and that the Trust
OL,14,Fdeliberately told the coroner that she
OL,15,Fdied of cancer and myotonic dystrophy.
